    <commentid>2184856</commentid>
    <comment_count>2</comment_count>
    <who name="Miles Parker">milesparker</who>
    <bug_when>2012-11-17 14:50:02 -0500</bug_when>
    <thetext>Yeah, this is a consequence of simply copying the behavior of Gerrit which satisfies the principle of least surprise. Unfortunately, the default behavior is really bad. I think we need to find a way to retain the match to the Gerrit Web UI (as sub-optimal as it is) while adding what people want. Perhaps something like &quot;My Open Changes&quot; (mirros gerrit) with an additional option &quot;My Open and Closed Changes&quot; or &quot;All My Changes&quot;. But both of those are really awkward. We could also add an &quot;Include Closed&quot; check box, but that&apos;s even more awkward.</thetext>
  </long_desc><long_desc isprivate="0" >
